init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You have no idea what JFK could mean by this, but you're intrigued.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Hesitantly, you call the number he's given in the letter and you speak to him.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Nonetheless, you speak to the man who claims to be JFK.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: JFK tells you that he's sending a plane for you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I'm sorry Barack, but you have to do this alone.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You have no choice in the matter."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You make up some nonsense about a new job.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You deflect questions about the job and try to change the subject.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The next morning, the mansion staff are gathered and ready to chauffeur you to the airport.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He tells you that he needs your help to do something tremendously important, and that it's up to you to stop a major threat.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Peace is restored again to both nations.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He says that he might indeed have need for you again in the future.
